### Assign default isolation segment

```
Definition
```

```http
PATCH /v3/organizations/:guid/relationships/default_isolation_segment HTTP/1.1
```

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/organizations/[guid]/relationships/default_isolation_segment" \
  -X PATCH \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -d '{
    "data": {
      "guid": "[iso-seg-guid]"
     }
   }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK

<%= yield_content :default_isolation_segment_relationship, '/v3/organizations/:guid/relationships/default_isolation_segment' %>
```

This endpoint sets the default isolation segment for a given organization.  Only Admins and Org Managers can set the default.
Only isolation segments that are entitled to the organization are eligible to be the default isolation segment.

Apps will not run in the new default isolation segment until they are restarted.

